    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nChanging `colorscheme` will change colors in the terminal buffer.\n\n<img width=\"1274\" height=\"1433\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4235893f-69d6-40b0-b822-d9c96fe74cc2\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:ter\n:color blue\n:ter\n:color hamabax\n:ter\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nColors stay identical to the terminal emulator.\n\n<img width=\"1274\" height=\"1433\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eedd4f81-7edf-4c9a-8c2a-ac38ccc92e33\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux, Linux 7.0.3-zen1-2-zen\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.17.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nOfficial Arch (extra) Repository",
