        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "This doesn't make sense.\n>'termguicolors' 'tgc'\tboolean\t(default off)\n>\t\t\tglobal\n>\tEnables 24-bit RGB color in the |TUI|.  Uses \"gui\" |:highlight|\n>\tattributes instead of \"cterm\" attributes. |guifg|\n>\tRequires an ISO-8613-3 compatible terminal.\n>\n>\tNvim will automatically attempt to determine if the host terminal\n>\tsupports 24-bit color and will enable this option if it does\n>\t(unless explicitly disabled by the user).\n\nNo where does it say, that 'tgc' now implements #26857. How does a colorscheme even decide which highlight to map to a terminal color? Which highlight-group controls terminal colors?",
